<br>
You (and your buddies) turn in the staffs (be careful of faction, etc.).  The *last* person to hand him one of the 3 staffs gets back a bag **that you can't open** which, according to the npc text, holds all 4 staffs (Arantir adds his own to your three).  As I said though, you can't actually open the bag to see the staffs inside.  You then take the &quot;bag&quot; to the dude in Temple of Solusek Ro in return for the epic.<br>
<br>
I'm too lazy atm to look up the exact spellings of the gnome and the dude in ToSR.<br>
